    "body": "**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\nHere is the PyGMT version:\r\n```python\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(R=\"10/70/-3/8\", J=\"X4i/3i\", B=\"a\")\r\nfig.psconvert(F=\"test_psconvert_int_options\", E=100, T=\"g\", I=True)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere is the GMT CLI version:\r\n```\r\ngmt begin map\r\ngmt basemap -R10/70/-3/8 -JX4i/3i -Ba\r\ngmt psconvert -E100 -Tg -I -Foutput\r\ngmt end\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Full error message**\r\n\r\n```\r\npsconvert [ERROR]: Option -I: No arguments given\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error is caused by the changes in https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/gmt/pull/5583. In the comment https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/gmt/pull/5583#issuecomment-892369066, @PaulWessel said \r\n> The old -I for using ICC profiles has been reborn as -N+i but no-arg -I is also parsed under backwards rules.\r\n\r\nIf I understand it correctly, `-I` should be changed to `-N+i`, and `-I` alone should also be supported, but actually it doesn't\r\n\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.3.0_6fd8408_2021.08.10\r\n",
